left></td><td align=right> <br> <a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm27.showPrevMessage?topicID=32.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm27.showNextMessage?topicID=32.topic"> Next Topic >> </a> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95% cellpadding=5 cellspacing=1><tr><td valign=top  class=headings><font color=#333399>Author</font></td><td valign=top  class=headings><font color=#333399>Comment</font></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthedruidsgrove.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=rtfm>rtfm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(10/2/01 1:28:28 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=32.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> No drive-by buffs and concentration</span><hr size=1> Just a note.<br>
<br>
All your buffs that you cast are counted against your &quot;Concentration&quot;.<br>
<br>
They all add up, if you have buffs on your pet, that will limit the buffs you can cast on your group members.<br>
<br>
Pet does not seem to take any concentration to cast or maintain.<br>
<br>
There is no way you can turn off the buffs on a player you cast on.  They have to die to do that.<br>
<br>
I think it is an ingenious way of having players group.  Buffing 'beggars' should not be a problem in this game. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubrairwolf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Brairwolf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(10/2/01 1:58:48 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=32.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: No drive-by buffs and concentration</span><hr size=1> Not completely true.  Most druid/warden/bard buffs are con based but not all.  Other class such as the enchanter buffs are not con based but timed. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/udasteel.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dasteel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(10/2/01 2:10:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=32.topic&index=2>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: No drive-by buffs and concentration</span><hr size=1> Actually, you can cancel the buffs you've cast.<br>
<br>
You can open your concentration panel, which shows every spell that is 'costing' you concentration. They are listed by spell name and character name. Shift-right-clicking on any spell in that list cancels it.<br>
<br>
So you can give a begger a buff, then cancel it as soon as they run off :) <p><i>It seemed like a good idea at the time ...</i></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthedruidsgrove.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=rtfm>rtfm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(10/2/01 2:44:29 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=32.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> ...</span><hr size=1> Thanks for the shift right click thingy. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthedruidsgrove.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=cayne>Cayne</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(10/2/01 6:02:37 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=32.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> No drive-by buffs and concentration</span><hr size=1> What happens in a group situation when the buffor goes link dead? Do all his buffs drop also? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ueckointhedarkness.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ecko in the darkness</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(10/2/01 6:21:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=32.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: No drive-by buffs and concentration</span><hr size=1>   Concentration slots like ncu slots?  Ohh boy looks like I really better play a melee clas...wait what was I writing about? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubrairwolf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Brairwolf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(10/2/01 6:34:42 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=32.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: No drive-by buffs and concentration</span><hr size=1> The way concentration spell work is you see a bar ( if you have it turned on) with a very easy to read bar graph that shows how much you have left to spare.  Looks like a standard HP type bar.  It does not tell you how many points you have.  <br>
<br>
Zones are huge, but if you zone buffs drop.<br>
If you camp, buffs drop.<br>
If your buffer zones, all his buffs drop.<br>
You die, buffs drop.<br>
Buffer dies, all buffs drop.<br>
<br>
It is not clear if concentration works like the mana pool does in EQ.  I can keep about 16 or so buffs going at a time.<br>
<br>
Upside to this, they don't wear off.  Also not all buffs stack even from the same person.  Some are group buffs and some a target buffs.  You can buff pets.  It does not look like group buffs help pets. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utudamorf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tudamorf</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://lag999.homestead.com/files/biggrin.gif width=15 height=15" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(10/3/01 8:57:41 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=32.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://lag999.homestead.com/files/rtfm.gif width=100 height=100></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: No drive-by buffs and concentration</span><hr size=1> rtfm says:  <b><i>All your buffs that you cast are counted against your "Concentration".</b></i><br>
<br>
Huh?  You mean every buff I cast on anyone counts as a concentration point (against me, not the target), and I have to die, zone, or camp if the target doesn't voluntarily get rid of them?  That sounds annoying and impractical to me, particularly if the concentration limit is not very high.<br>
<br>
Suppose I cast a few buffs on a friend because I'm soloing, and after the friend leaves I join a group.  I have to message the friend to drop the buffs, or go through a camp-wait-logoff-wait-logon ritual (and have the friend's buffs drop unceremoniously, possibly in the middle of combat) to avoid the limitations.<br>
<br>
This doesn't, by the way, prevent buff beggars.  It just ups the stakes for the buff, so instead of "buff plz" you'll get "buff plz PLZ PLZ PLZ i rly need it!!!!!"  As we all know, buff beggars care about themselves, not the person they're asking.  <img src=http://lag999.homestead.com/files/rolleyes.gif><br>
<br>
[Edit] Another question:  if buffs don't fade, aren't primary-buff classes put in a rather awkward position?  They'll cast the buff, then cease to be useful, because they won't be needed to keep the buff going.  I can imagine mules left online for the sole purpose of keeping a buff going, kind of like the mana song in EQ. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utudamorf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tudamorf</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://lag999.homestead.com/files/biggrin.gif width=15 height=15" BORDER=0> at: 10/3/01 6:05:52 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ugoldmundtargari.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Goldmund TargaRi</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(10/3/01 9:32:44 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=32.topic&index=8>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: No drive-by buffs and concentration</span><hr size=1> Actually Tudamorf, you can cancel any concentration based buff that you have cast on anyone.  The concentration panel shows all the concentration based buffs that you've cast, and who is wearing them.  To cancel one of the buffs you just shift and right-click on the persons name.  So if you toss someone a conc buff and need that conc later on, just cancel it off of them.  The caster is in complete control on this.  <br>
<br>
Also, not all buffs are concentration based.  There are tons of buffs that are on a timer and need to be refreshed. <p><img src=http://www.alltel.net/~mr81645/godzillasig55.jpg></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthedruidsgrove.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=rtfm>rtfm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(10/3/01 10:09:39 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=32.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> ...</span><hr size=1> Good points.<br>
<br>
I do have a self only buff, a self hast spell, that is timer based and does not count against conc.<br>
<br>
And the shift right click does the trick for removing a buff.<br>
<br>
Buff mules,,, good idea;)<br>
<br>
I can get out about 12 buffs before I am out of conc.<br>
<br>
It is a trade off of spells that do not wear off. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubrairwolf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Brairwolf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(10/3/01 10:38:36 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=32.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ...</span><hr size=1> Carefull with the self haste buff (talking the attack speed buff)<br>
It is not a con buff but it does drain your power(mana). <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthedruidsgrove.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=rtfm>rtfm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(10/3/01 11:36:43 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=32.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> ...</span><hr size=1> What do you mean it drains your power?<br>
<br>
When you cast it?<br>
<br>
Or during melee? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/udasteel.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dasteel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(10/3/01 12:02:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=32.topic&index=12>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: No drive-by buffs and concentration</span><hr size=1> <i>"Huh? You mean every buff I cast on anyone counts as a concentration point (against me, not the target), and I have to die, zone, or camp if the target doesn't voluntarily get rid of them? That sounds annoying and impractical to me, particularly if the concentration limit is not very high."</i><br>
<br>
As I said (five posts above yours):<br>
<i>"Actually, you can cancel the buffs you've cast.<br>
<br>
You can open your concentration panel, which shows every spell that is 'costing' you concentration. They are listed by spell name and character name. Shift-right-clicking on any spell in that list cancels it.<br>
<br>
So you can give a begger a buff, then cancel it as soon as they run off :) "</i><br>
<br>
======================================<br>
<br>
<i>"What do you mean it drains your power?"</i><br>
<br>
Some of the haste and damage buffs (especially group ones) start to drain power the instant you cast them. They will, over time, drain your power to zero, at which point they end. Of course, you can cancel them before that if you want.<br>
<br>
I'm not sure which spells follow this rule, but I have two Warden buffs that work like that (damage increase and haste).<br>
<br>
They're kind of like the EQ Shaman spell line that drains mana while it's up.<br>
<br>
I also have (as a Warden) a run speed buff that seems to stay up forever, not take concentration, and not drain mana (after the initial, cheap, cast cost). It even lives through combat, although it's 'supressed' (SoW type spells don't work through combat). Once I stop fighting, it re-activates, without a recast. It's also a group buff :)<br>
 <p><i>It seemed like a good idea at the time ...</i></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usaurincotg.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Saurin CoTG</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(10/3/01 12:35:14 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=32.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: No drive-by buffs and concentration</span><hr size=1> The Warden run speed spell acts as a song (similar to a bard) such that is pulses, uses no additional mana and does not take up concentration points. <br>
<br>
Prior to the NDA being lifted I had mentioned in a previous thread that there really isn't buff begging in this game, the concentration point system is why.  As a caster and primary buffer ( the druid) cannot afford to waste valuable concentration points on folks that are not in my party.  If you happen to be in a full 8 person group, you will not have enough concentration points to fully buff every member of your party.  You will have to pick and choose who gets what buff.  Some will like this system, some won't.<br>
<br>
On the buff mule concept, the game will log you out after a certain period of time if you aren't doing anything.  I have not tested whether this occurs if you have an active concentration buff on someone else or not although pulsing songs seems to avoid logout.  <br>
<br>
